given.name: EmptyInputAndEmptyOutput
given.documentation:
The example tests how requests and responses are serialized when there's no request or response members.

While this should be rare, code generators must support this.

cases.description: Empty input serializes no extra query params

given.name: NoInputAndOutput
given.documentation:
The example tests how requests and responses are serialized when there's no request payload or response members.

While this should be rare, code generators must support this.

cases.description: No input serializes no payload
Compression algorithm encoding is appended to the Content-Encoding header.

Compression algorithm encoding is appended to the Content-Encoding header, and the
user-provided content-encoding is NOT in the Content-Encoding header since HTTP binding
traits are ignored in the ec2Query protocol.

given.name: QueryTimestamps
given.documentation:
This test serializes timestamps.

  1. Timestamps are serialized as RFC 3339 date-time values by default.
  2. A timestampFormat trait on a member changes the format.
  3. A timestampFormat trait on the shape targeted by the member changes the format.

cases.description: Serializes timestamps
